        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 9:22PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Anthonyville, or 8 miles southwest of West Memphis, moving north at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mound City, Kate, Louise, West Memphis, Brice, Cunningham Corner,
Amanea, Edmondson, Wyandoke, St Clair, Harvard, Presidents Island,
Neuhardt, Simsboro, Briark, T O Fuller State Park, Crittenden,
Riceville, Vincent, and Hulbert.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
